Made CropViewController class open to allow for some extra flexibility - overrides of standard UIViewController methods like viewWillAppear or prefersStatusBarHidden.
Added TOCropViewControllerToolbarPositionHidden option for TOCropViewControllerToolbarPosition to enable adding custom UI controls for Cancel, rotate and Done.
Added hidesNavigationBar for TOCropViewController to allow navigation bar being shown when embedded in UINavigationViewController. This adds more freedom to the users to create interfaces more fitting their apps design.

Fix to crash when Done is pressed while the library was imported from another project. Exception was unknown selector (UIImage *)croppedImageWithFrame:(CGRect)frame angle:(NSInteger)angle circularClip:(BOOL)circular scale:(CGFloat)scale. For some reason this crash did not happen when running just the example project.

Adding a new property on TOCropView aspectRatioAllowDimensionSwap, which is exposed via a get/set on TOCropViewController as aspectRatioLockAllowDimensionSwap. This property is used when combined with aspectRatioLockEnabled to allow for TOCropViewController to swap the croppers dimensions for custom aspect ratios, like the preset ones. By default this is set to know to preserve existing behavior.
